notes: South African Innings
50 up in 43 mins off 60 balls including 4 fours and a six
100 up in 102 mins off 147 balls including 9 fours and a six
3rd Wicket 50 Partnership in 57 mins off 85 balls including 5 fours (Kallis 19, Gibbs 24)
HH Gibbs 50 in 85 mins off 73 balls including 6 fours
JH Kallis 50 in 108 mins off 71 balls including 5 fours
150 up in 135 mins off 206 balls including 12 fours and a six
2nd Wicket 100 Partnership in 90 mins off 144 balls including 8 fours (Kallis 35, Gibbs 54)
200 up in 172 mins off 259 balls including 15 fours and 2 sixes
250 up in 198 mins off 290 balls including 16 fours and 7 sixes
5th Wicket 50 partnership in 25 mins off 29 balls including 1 four and 4 sixes (Kemp 34, Prince 13)
JM Kemp 50 in 51 mins off 34 balls including 3 fours and a six
JM Kemp achived his best score for One Day Internationals for South Africa

JH Kallis and HH Gibbs surpassed the 3rd Wicket partnership record for a match played at Newlands beating the previous best of 123 held by MA Taylor and ME Waugh for Australia vs South Africa in 1993/94
They also bettered their own 3rd Wicket partnership record vs England beating the 134 vs England at Bloemfontein in 2004/05
England Innigs
50 up in 55 mins off 75 balls including 6 fours
100 up in 104 mins off 137 balls including 11 fours and a six
KP Pietersen 50 in 77 mins off 60 balls including 5 fours and a six
Official Attendance : 20,652
150 up in 148 mins off 198 balls including 12 fours and 3 sixes
